Review: Dark and screwy, I did feel for him when he jumped the subway turnstile and immediately got yelled at.

The ending song had a lyric that went “I had a dream about a boy in a castle, and he was dancing like a cat on the stairs” and this is just one of the many things that goes very hard in this movie. This movie really did have it all.
Spooky slow burn, great line reading of “you goddamn son of a bitch”

Movie: David Holmes: The Boy Who Lived

Review: My friends and I could fend off the predator if given the opportunity, I bet
Surprised at how divisive this movie seemed to be, it’s good!
His annoying tone while answering the chat throughout the whole movie got me, thought it was a pretty funny bit.

Movie: Wallace & Gromit: The Curse of the Were-Rabbit
Review: I wish I would have seen this as a child, it could have been my favorite movie
Such an absurd chain of events happen in this movie, I loved it. Very fun to see on the big screen.
Bing Crosby is short for Bingbong Crosby
Colin from Whose Line is the antagonist in this if anyone was wondering
Some of the most absurd child acting I have ever witnessed in a movie
